  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide access to education, health and hygiene support to Rag Picking community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">200 children receive bridge education; clean water, nutrition and medical check-up to improve children&apos;s health;Sensitization of parents to the importance of education and smooth re-entry to school for children, basic awareness on health and hygiene. facilitate admission of children in the main schools.  The activities will ensure that children health and hygiene habits will improve leading to healthy life.   By going to school, children are expected less time on garbage collection and more time on academics.  Awareness to parents will ensure that more children are turned out to school and less drop outs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid fundraising and supporter team supported phia foundation  to get a three year project for addressing education, health and hygiene needs of rag picking communities based in NCR from Monsoon Accessorize Trust, UK.  Phia Foundation is directly implementing a project on providing bridge school facilities to rag picking community.Mobilisation and awareness raising with community, community leaders and local stakeholders.  Activities such as regular honorarium to be given to 2 fellows and technical cost to be converted to use it for designing syllabus and curriculum for the children by the trained fellow.  Sanitization, awareness drive would be taken up regularly;Capacity building trainings: Child Rights, POCSO, Child&apos;s expression, etc.Sport and important day celebration in local area ;Supply of clean water and nutritious food for children to improve the immunity; medical check ups and support to family for accessing treatment from hospitals;  Regular meeting with parents, teachers of the school where the children are enrolled to know the progress and continuity of education. Puppetry training to senior children to conduct street plays and children platform to raise awareness on education and other social messages.</narrative>
  </description>
